# HTML Rules

## Page structure

Every page must follow the established site structure:

```html
<nav class="site-nav">...</nav>
<main>...</main>
<footer>...</footer>
```

## Semantics

- Use semantic HTML5 elements: `<article>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<time>`, etc.
- Heading hierarchy must be continuous — never skip levels (h1 → h2 → h3, not h1 → h3)
- External links that open a new tab: add `rel="noopener noreferrer"`; add `aria-label` when visible
  link text is not self-describing
- 2-space indent throughout

## Styles & scripts

- Link only to `assets/jeffrey.css` — never add `<style>` blocks or inline `style=""` attributes
- No `<script>` tags unless absolutely necessary — the site is intentionally JS-minimal
- No external font imports, CDN links, or tracking pixels

## New page checklist

1. Add entry to `vite.config.js` rollupOptions.input map
2. Copy nav structure from `index.html` for consistency
3. Verify rendering at 768px mobile breakpoint in `mise run dev`
4. Run `mise run ci` before done

## Experiments

Pages under `experiments/` are excluded from CI and deployment — safe to prototype freely there.
